# Prefer shadcn/ui

When adding or replacing UI controls (Select, Button, Dialog, Input, Dropdown, Checkbox, Tabs, etc.):

1. **Use shadcn/ui first** from `@/components/ui/*`.
2. If a component is missing, add it with `npx shadcn@latest add <component>` before inventing a custom one.
3. Prefer composing shadcn primitives over native HTML form controls when the control needs custom chrome (e.g. Select triggers, menus, dialogs).
4. Keep brand colors where the product already uses them (e.g. `#0071e3`) by className overrides on shadcn components when needed.
5. Still follow icon guidelines: lucide-react only, no emoji icons.
6. Do not reinvent Select / Dropdown / Dialog / Popover with hand-rolled divs if a shadcn component exists.

Existing one-off custom layouts (marketing sections, galleries) can stay custom; form controls and app chrome should migrate toward shadcn over time.
